---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import BreadcrumbSchema from '../components/schema/BreadcrumbSchema.astro';
import { SITE } from '../consts';
---
<BaseLayout
  title="Features"
  description="A closer look at Underdial: check any watch under $1,000, spot redundant buys, find cheaper ways to the same style, audit your whole box, browse the catalog, and track your rotation."
  path="/features"
>
  <Fragment slot="head">
    <BreadcrumbSchema crumbs={[{ name: 'Features', url: `${SITE.url}/features` }]} />
  </Fragment>

  <span class="eyebrow" style="text-align:center;display:block;">{SITE.name}</span>
  <h1>Features</h1>
  <p class="effective">Everything Underdial does, in one place.</p>

  <!-- Check any watch -->
  <section class="feature-row">
    <div class="feature-row-copy">
      <span class="eyebrow">WatchFit Check</span>
      <h3>Should I buy this watch?</h3>
      <p>Search the watch you are eyeing and the WatchFit advisor runs it through five checks: your budget, your wrist size, your existing box, the archetype spread, and the price-to-value band. Then it gives a plain verdict, smart add, redundant, or wrong fit.</p>
      <p>It is a second opinion before you spend, not a hype reel. Every verdict comes with the reasoning behind it, so you know <em>why</em>, not just yes or no.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="feature-row-shot">
      <img
        src="/assets/screenshots/check.png"
        alt="Underdial WatchFit check screen showing a verdict for a searched watch with the reasoning behind it"
        loading="eager"
        width="260"
      />
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Spot the redundancy -->
  <section class="feature-row feature-row--reverse">
    <div class="feature-row-shot">
      <img
        src="/assets/screenshots/redundant.png"
        alt="Redundancy flag showing a watch that duplicates an archetype already in the user's box"
        loading="lazy"
        width="260"
      />
    </div>
    <div class="feature-row-copy">
      <span class="eyebrow">Redundancy Check</span>
      <h3>Stop buying the same watch twice</h3>
      <p>Already own a black mechanical diver? Underdial tells you before you buy a second one. It compares <strong>archetype</strong>, <strong>movement family</strong>, and <strong>dial</strong> against what is already in your box.</p>
      <p>The third field watch on a brown strap is not a new watch, it is the same decision again. Underdial calls it out so your money goes toward a slot you actually have open.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Cheaper alternatives -->
  <section class="feature-row">
    <div class="feature-row-copy">
      <span class="eyebrow">Value Finder</span>
      <h3>Cheaper ways to the same style</h3>
      <p>For any watch you check, Underdial surfaces lower-priced pieces in the same archetype and movement class, with the savings spelled out in dollars.</p>
      <p>The look you want often exists for less. If a homage or a quieter brand gets you 90% of the way for half the price, you deserve to see it before you commit.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="feature-row-shot">
      <img
        src="/assets/screenshots/alternatives.png"
        alt="Cheaper alternatives list showing lower-priced watches in the same archetype with savings amounts"
        loading="lazy"
        width="260"
      />
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Box Audit -->
  <section class="feature-row">
    <div class="feature-row-copy" style="grid-column:1 / -1;text-align:center;max-width:640px;margin:0 auto;">
      <span class="eyebrow">Box Audit</span>
      <h3>Audit your whole collection</h3>
      <p>See your box's spread at a glance, archetypes, movements, dial colors, case sizes, with redundancies and gaps surfaced automatically.</p>
      <p>Instead of buying more of what you already have, find the slot you are actually missing. The Box Audit turns a pile of watches into a map of what to add next.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Browse the catalog -->
  <section class="feature-row">
    <div class="feature-row-copy">
      <span class="eyebrow">Browse</span>
      <h3>Browse the under-$1,000 catalog</h3>
      <p>Filter and search a curated catalog of watches that all sit under the $1,000 ceiling. Narrow by archetype, movement, case size, brand, and price.</p>
      <p>No watch in the catalog is out of your band by definition, every result is something you could actually buy.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="feature-row-shot">
      <img
        src="/assets/screenshots/browse.png"
        alt="Browse screen showing the filterable catalog of watches under $1,000"
        loading="lazy"
        width="260"
      />
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Rotation -->
  <section class="feature-row feature-row--reverse">
    <div class="feature-row-shot">
      <img
        src="/assets/screenshots/rotation.png"
        alt="Rotation screen showing which watches in the box are worn most and least"
        loading="lazy"
        width="260"
      />
    </div>
    <div class="feature-row-copy">
      <span class="eyebrow">Rotation</span>
      <h3>See what you actually wear</h3>
      <p>Track your rotation so the watch you reach for every day and the one that never leaves the box both become obvious.</p>
      <p>Knowing which pieces earn their place is the cheapest way to buy better, it tells you what kind of watch you really wear, not the kind you thought you would.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="cta-section">
    <h2 class="section-title" style="margin-top:0;">Ready when you are</h2>
    <p class="cta-body">
      Underdial lands on the App Store soon. Questions or feedback?
      Email <a href={`mailto:${SITE.supportEmail}`}>{SITE.supportEmail}</a>.
    </p>
    <div class="cta-row">
      {SITE.appStoreUrl ? (
        <a class="btn" href={SITE.appStoreUrl}>Download on iOS</a>
      ) : (
        <span class="btn btn--disabled">App Store (Coming Soon)</span>
      )}
    </div>
  </section>

  <Footer />
</BaseLayout>
